{"lemma":"تَبِعاتُ","slug":"تَبِعاتُ","root":"ت.ب.ع","root_slug":"ت-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3724","n3735"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of تَابِع (tābiʕ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of تَابِع (tābiʕ)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3724","headword_ar":"تَبِعَهُ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAEapN","text_ar":"تَبَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He followed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked, behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a people, or company of men: (S:) or [in the CK “ and ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, when the latter had passed by him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEahu","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (Lth, S, K *) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEahu","text_ar":"اَتْبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, Mgh, K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEotuhumo","text_ar":"اَتْبَعْتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I overtook them, they having gone before me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, * A'Obeyd, S, Msb, * K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEotuhumo","text_ar":"تَبِعْتُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, K:) Akh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEotuhu","text_ar":"تَبِعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEotuhu","text_ar":"اَتْبَعْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same: and hence the saying in the Kur [xxxvii. 10],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ihaAbN vaAqibN","text_ar":"شِهَابٌ ثَاقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^atobaEahu","text_ar":"فَاَتْبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a shooting star piercing the darkness by its light overtaketh him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and the saying in the same [vii. 174], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^atobaEahu","text_ar":"فَاَتْبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayoTaAnu","text_ar":"الشَّيْطَانُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the devil overtook him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":294},{"kind":"text","text":"the saying in the same [xx. 81],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firoEawonu","text_ar":"فِرْعَوْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^atobaEahumo","text_ar":"فَاَتْبَعَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijunuwdihi","text_ar":"بِجُنُودِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and Pharaoh overtook them with his troops:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"almost did so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, K:) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made his troops to follow them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to some, being redundant: (Bd:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEahu","text_ar":"اَتْبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed his footsteps;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought him, following him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEahumo","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"followed them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they had passed by him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEahumo","text_ar":"تَبِعَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY A^atobaEotuhumo","text_ar":"حَتَّى اَتْبَعْتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zilotu A^at~abiEuhumo","text_ar":"مَا زِلْتُ اَتَّبِعُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ceased not to follow them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until I overtook them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd:) Fr says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEa","text_ar":"اَتْبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is better than ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEa","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after, him, when the latter person was going along;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but when you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEotuhu","text_ar":"اَتْبَعْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is as though [you meant that] you followed his footsteps: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فُلَانًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEa","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as in the L and TA, but perhaps a mistake for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEa","text_ar":"اَتْبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed him, desiring to do evil to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as Pharaoh followed Moses: (L, TA:) some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEotu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"تَبِعْتُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tubuwEN","text_ar":"تُبُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I went after the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEa Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"تَبِعَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAEN","text_ar":"تَبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of actions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEa AlA_imaAma","text_ar":"تَبِعَ الاـِمَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed the Imám"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by doing as he did"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [but in this last sense, more commonly,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEahu","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did like as he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[another]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquroA=na","text_ar":"القُرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEa","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed the Kurán as his guide; did according to what is in it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEahu","text_ar":"تَابَعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY ka*aA","text_ar":"على كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaAbaEapN","text_ar":"مُتَابَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibaAEN","text_ar":"تِبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imitated him, in the affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imitated him, in doing such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS:) [but this last phrase has another meaning: see 3.] In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yutobaEu binaArK A_ilaY Alqabori","text_ar":"لَا يُتْبَعُ بِنَارٍ اـِلَى القَبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in which the verb may be pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEa","text_ar":"تَبِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaEa","text_ar":"اَتْبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] or, accord. to one relation, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA yut~abaEu","text_ar":"لا يُتَّبَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", each in the pass. form, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fire shall not be made to follow to the grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though it may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one shall not follow with fire to the grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said that] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to render the verb transitive. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEotu Alr~ajula biHaq~iY","text_ar":"تَبِعْتُ الرَّجُلَ بِحَقِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEotuhu","text_ar":"تَابَعْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaAbaEapN","text_ar":"مُتَابَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbaAEN","text_ar":"تبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bh","text_ar":"به"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~abaEotuhu","text_ar":"اِتَّبَعْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I prosecuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sued, the man for my right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The saying in the Kur [ii. 173],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@lomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِا@لْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@t~ibaAEN","text_ar":"فَا@تِّبَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosecution"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the bloodwit [shall be made"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with lenity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEa","text_ar":"تَبِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the aor.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatobaE","text_ar":"يَتْبَع"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurs in a trad., [see 4,] (Mgh, TA,) pronounced by the relaters of trads. with teshdeed, [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yat~abiE","text_ar":"يَتَّبِع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (TA,) also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accepted a reference from his debtor to another for the payment of what was owed to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA. *)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Mgh","Lth","Fr","TA","Bd","L","PS"]},{"entry_id":"n3735","headword_ar":"تَبِعَةٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibaAEapN","text_ar":"تِبَاعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; (T, S, O, L, K;) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an action: and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a claim which one seeks to obtain for an injury,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injurious treatment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O, L, K; and so the Msb in explanation of the former word:) the former is also explained as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, annexed to property, claimed from the possessor of the property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) pl. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEaAtN","text_ar":"تَبِعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibaAEaAtN","text_ar":"تِبَاعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"zamana Alt~aqaH~umi waAlmajaAEaho \n                      \n                     \n                        A^akalato Haniyfapu rab~ahaA\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      suwo'a AlEawaAqibi waAlt~ibaAEaho \n                      \n                     \n                        lamo yaHo*aruwA mino rab~ihimo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Haneefeh ate their lord, in the time of experiencing dearth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility, and hunger: they did not fear, from their lord, the evil of the results, and the consequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of their action]: for they had taken to themselves a god consisting of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hayos","text_ar":"حَيْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. dates mixed with clarified butter and the preparation of milk called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiT","text_ar":"اَقِط"},{"kind":"text","text":", kneaded together,] and worshipped it for some time; then famine befell them, and they ate it. (S.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Ealayohi mina A@ll~`hi fiY h`*aA tabiEapN","text_ar":"مَا عَلَيْهِ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ فِى هٰذَا تَبِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibaAEapN","text_ar":"تِبَاعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not, against him, on the part of God, in this, any claim on account of wrong-doing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}